title.narrative: Maximizing Agricultural Revenue and Key Enterprises in Targeted Sectors (MARKETS) II

description.narrative: (Nigeria): ..MARKETS II improves the incomes and nutrition of poor smallholder farmers through proven private sector demand driven interventions. The project focuses on farmers with five hectares or less of land and small-scale agricultural support services along targeted value chains. . .FY 2016, MARKETS II will support 200,000 farmers to access finance to purchase agro-inputs and expand production and sales, establish over 100 technology demonstration plots and train farmers in three states. It will also collaborate with Partnership Initiatives in the Niger Delta (PIND), an initiative with Chevron to link 1,000 out-growers to industrial processors. The project will also train 15,000 farmers on business skills and nutrition.. .A total of some 193,000 farmers are expected to apply new technologies and management practices on approximately 229,000 hectares of land. The value of new private sector investments is expected to reach $5.5 million. .
